这个死者就是豪夫
This dead guy was Hauffe.

185
00:10:58,530 --> 00:11:00,940
科尔杀了他在史塔西的队友
Kohl killed his Stasi teammate.

186
00:11:01,300 --> 00:11:02,920
而他还会继续杀人
And he will kill again.

187
00:11:03,090 --> 00:11:06,740
我不知道你是谁  也不知道你怎么找到这里
I don't know who you are or how you know to be here,

188
00:11:07,320 --> 00:11:09,140
但这一切只是个开始
But this is just the beginning.

189
00:11:09,150 --> 00:11:12,030
而今天会是漫长的一天
Then this is gonna be a long day.

190
00:11:28,560 --> 00:11:30,240
芬奇  这还有其他人
Finch, I got company.

191
00:11:30,620 --> 00:11:33,600
BND  德国情报局的
B.N.D.-- German intelligence.

192
00:11:34,540 --> 00:11:36,650
他似乎知道这里发生了什么
He seemed to know what went down here.

193
00:11:37,020 --> 00:11:40,420
他也很确定科尔会再开杀戒
He also seemed sure Kohl would kill again.

194
00:11:45,440 --> 00:11:46,350
我是弗斯科警探
Detective Fusco.

195
00:11:46,350 --> 00:11:48,620
你有个匿名线报  莱奈尔
Anonymous tip for you, Lionel.

196
00:11:50,860 --> 00:11:52,490
你不要再往这里打我电话
You got to stop calling me here.

197
00:11:52,490 --> 00:11:54,220
西城有一起谋杀案
Homicide in the west village.

198
00:11:54,220 --> 00:11:56,700
凶手应该还要杀更多的人
I think the shooter might have others planned today.

199
00:11:57,040 --> 00:12:00,200
我在现场给你留了个小礼物
I left you a care package at the scene.

200
00:12:00,200 --> 00:12:02,600
我要你查清楚他都知道什么
I need you to find out whatever he knows.

201
00:12:02,600 --> 00:12:03,870
好吧  但我什么做不了
Yeah, well, I can't do anything

202
00:12:03,870 --> 00:12:05,100
除非有人报案
Till someone calls in a crime.

203
00:12:05,100 --> 00:12:07,440
你马上就会接到  "有枪击"
You'll get a call-- "Shots fired."

204
00:12:07,440 --> 00:12:09,820
那儿有枪击吗
Were there shots fired?

205
00:12:12,510 --> 00:12:14,090
现在有了
There were now.

206
00:12:21,020 --> 00:12:22,680
豪夫死了
Hauffe's dead.

207
00:12:22,820 --> 00:12:24,720
科尔的下一个目标是谁
Who's next on Kohl's hit list?

208
00:12:24,720 --> 00:12:27,090
我拿到一个德国探员的加密电话
I took an encrypted phone from that German agent.

209
00:12:27,090 --> 00:12:30,670
所有短信都被屏蔽了  除了他们在读的那条
Every text is blocked except for the one they were reading--

210
00:12:30,740 --> 00:12:31,980
朱利安・温纳
Julian Werner.

211
00:12:34,410 --> 00:12:36,260
温纳是个华尔街的律师
Werner is a Wall street lawyer,

212
00:12:36,270 --> 00:12:37,580
并且
And...

213
00:12:39,140 --> 00:12:40,500
温纳其实就是沃尼克
Werner is really Wernick--

214
00:12:40,500 --> 00:12:42,470
那个伪造者
The forger.

215
00:12:42,470 --> 00:12:45,550
科尔的小组都隐姓埋名生活在纽约
Kohl's entire team is living under aliases in New York.

216
00:12:45,640 --> 00:12:48,480
退隐的绝佳场所吧  芬奇
The perfect place to disappear, right, Finch?

217
00:12:48,480 --> 00:12:50,970
这些人都曾经是他的队友
These people were his teammates.

218
00:12:50,970 --> 00:12:53,640
为什么过了二十年  他还要追杀他们
Why would he be hunting them two decades later?

219
00:12:53,640 --> 00:12:55,180
科尔消失得无影无踪
Kohl vanishes without a trace,

220
00:12:55,180 --> 00:12:58,390
而他的队友却在纽约过上无忧无虑的日子
and his teammates end up living cushy lives in New York.

221
00:12:58,390 --> 00:13:00,090
可能他是为了什么而复仇...
This could be revenge for something--

222
00:13:00,090 --> 00:13:01,910
比我们了解的要复杂得多
maybe more than we know.

223
00:13:01,910 --> 00:13:03,890
-没准和他妻子的死有关  -那场车祸
- The wife's death? - The car crash.

224
00:13:03,890 --> 00:13:06,930
她死于87年  同一年他就消失了
She died in '87, the same year he disappeared.

225
00:13:06,930 --> 00:13:09,660
如果车祸是假的我一眼就能看出来
And I know a staged accident when I see it.

226
00:13:09,670 --> 00:13:12,410
我们得赶在科尔之前找到沃尼克
We need to get to Wernick before Kohl does.

227
00:13:38,620 --> 00:13:40,940
我以为你死了
I thought you were dead.

228
00:13:42,360 --> 00:13:44,120
看来你还带着针啊
Still with the needle, I see.

229
00:13:48,040 --> 00:13:49,780
上面涂了什么
What is it coated with?

230
00:13:49,840 --> 00:13:51,680
发作很快的东西
Something fast.

231
00:13:52,940 --> 00:13:55,400
起码我还能为老同事做到这些
It's the least I could do for an old colleague.

232
00:13:55,400 --> 00:13:56,420
我还有多久
How long have I got?

233
00:13:58,220 --> 00:13:59,290
足够久了
Long enough.

234
00:14:00,970 --> 00:14:02,380
你的口音呢  组长
Where is your accent, Hauptmann?

235
00:14:02,650 --> 00:14:03,950
别人建议我们...
We were advised...

236
00:14:05,240 --> 00:14:06,710
隐没在美国人之中
to blend in America.

237
00:14:07,740 --> 00:14:09,370
今天早上我去看豪夫了
I saw Hauffe this morning.

238
00:14:09,860 --> 00:14:12,080
他是个出色的情报官
He was a good case officer.

239
00:14:12,520 --> 00:14:14,900
这么多年来一直保存着你的信息
He kept information on you all these years.

240
00:14:19,030 --> 00:14:20,050
你还记得
Do you remember...

241
00:14:21,120 --> 00:14:22,570
我的安雅吗
My Anja?

242
00:14:24,550 --> 00:14:25,740
我给温纳的助理打了电话
I called Werner's assistant.

243
00:14:25,740 --> 00:14:28,120
他每天中午都在同一个地方用餐
He has lunch at the same place every day.

244
00:14:28,120 --> 00:14:29,270
我这就去
I'm on my way.

245
00:14:30,330 --> 00:14:31,090
我记得
I remember.

246
00:14:31,940 --> 00:14:33,950
我不知道他们也在追杀她
I didn't know they would go after her, too.

247
00:14:35,580 --> 00:14:38,850
但就算杀了我  她也不能复生  乌里希
But killing me won't bring her back, Ulrich.

248
00:14:41,860 --> 00:14:46,020
我告诉她  我会保护她
I told her I would keep her safe.

249
00:14:46,910 --> 00:14:48,570
你怎么了  乌里希
What happened to you, Ulrich?

250
00:14:50,200 --> 00:14:51,130
我为我的罪孽
I paid...

251
00:14:52,530 --> 00:14:53,370
付出了代价
for my sins,

252
00:14:53,920 --> 00:14:56,240
你的罪  整个组的罪
For yours, for the team.

253
00:14:58,480 --> 00:15:00,720
那些抓住我的人把我关在一个洞里
The people who caught me kept me in a hole,

254
00:15:01,670 --> 00:15:05,520
可我从没停止过思考  策划
But I never stopped thinking, planning.

255
00:15:06,700 --> 00:15:09,520
那是很久以前的事了  我已经忘了
It was long ago. I let myself forget.

256
00:15:11,090 --> 00:15:12,790
对我而言遗忘太奢侈
I did not have that luxury.

257
00:15:14,100 --> 00:15:15,930
我们所作的都是错的
It was wrong what we did.

258
00:15:19,220 --> 00:15:21,040
你接下来要对付史戴勒吗
You'll go after Steiller next?

259
00:15:23,950 --> 00:15:24,710
那么
Then...

260
00:15:27,870 --> 00:15:29,920
保重  老朋友
Be at peace, my old friend.

261
00:15:38,070 --> 00:15:39,320
快报警
Call 911.

262
00:15:42,350 --> 00:15:44,850
速派救护车至19街43号
I need an ambulance at 43 19th street--

263
00:15:44,850 --> 00:15:46,920
卡夫吧咖啡馆
Craftbar cafe.

264
00:15:46,920 --> 00:15:48,720
女士  请靠后
Ma'am, stand back, please.

265
00:15:49,730 --> 00:15:51,100
借过
Excuse me.

266
00:15:52,930 --> 00:15:55,200
脉博微弱  心跳过速  血压 70/30
Weak pulse, but tachycardic-- B.P. is 70/30.

267
00:15:55,200 --> 00:15:57,300
呼吸急促  症状显示内部窒息
Shallow respiration, signs of internal asphyxia.

268
00:15:57,300 --> 00:15:59,410
出现抽搐  癫痫发作了
Convulsions-- guy's having a seizure.

269
00:16:05,740 --> 00:16:06,590
喂
Hey!

270
00:16:20,330 --> 00:16:21,860
你不能呼吸
You can't breathe.

271
00:16:21,860 --> 00:16:24,100
你的鼻腔跟口腔里满是泡沫
You have foam in your nose and your mouth.

272
00:16:24,100 --> 00:16:26,210
是氰化物
It's hydrocyanic acid.

273
00:16:26,360 --> 00:16:29,270
他们在四分钟内就能找到我们
Now, they're going to find us in four minutes.

274
00:16:29,270 --> 00:16:32,450
我能救你  但是你得跟我坦白
I can save you, but you need to talk.

275
00:16:35,580 --> 00:16:39,850
科尔为何而来  为什么他要对付你们每个人
What did Kohl come for? Why is he after all of you?

276
00:16:39,850 --> 00:16:43,600
科尔追杀过他们的线人
Kohl was killing their informants.

277
00:16:44,240 --> 00:16:46,320
美国人要他消失
The Americans wanted him gone.

278
00:16:46,320 --> 00:16:48,220
于是你们就交出了科尔
So you gave them Kohl.

279
00:16:48,220 --> 00:16:51,100
他们给了我们新生活
They offered us a new life.

280
00:16:52,260 --> 00:16:55,410
我们就拿乌里希做了交易
We traded Ulrich.

281
00:16:55,590 --> 00:16:57,870
你曾是他的队友
You were his team...

282
00:16:57,870 --> 00:16:59,320
他的朋友
His friends.

283
00:17:00,270 --> 00:17:02,870
这不是个老兵应得的下场
A soldier deserves better.

284
00:17:02,870 --> 00:17:06,070
我给你打这些  你就有救了
I give you these, and you live.

285
00:17:06,080 --> 00:17:08,100
你叛逃之后发生了什么
What happened after you defected?

286
00:17:08,100 --> 00:17:12,180
他们跟我说科尔投奔了苏联人
They told us Kohl ran to the soviets--

287
00:17:12,180 --> 00:17:13,650
他和安雅
He and Anja.

288
00:17:14,740 --> 00:17:17,430
美国人就去抓他
The Americans went for him.

289
00:17:19,660 --> 00:17:21,230
他们也杀了安雅
They got her, too.

290
00:17:21,490 --> 00:17:23,170
那场车祸
The car accident.

291
00:17:23,870 --> 00:17:24,860
对
Yes.

292
00:17:24,860 --> 00:17:27,200
科尔接下来是要找谁
Who will Kohl go after next?

293
00:17:27,200 --> 00:17:28,330
史...
St--

294
00:17:28,330 --> 00:17:30,840
史戴勒
Steiller...

295
00:17:31,110 --> 00:17:32,730
他跟你们一起叛逃了吗
He defected with the rest of you?

296
00:17:32,740 --> 00:17:34,980
喂  他的化名是什么
Hey? What's his alias?

297
00:17:44,240 --> 00:17:46,680
我救下了那个律师  但是科尔还没完
I kept the lawyer alive, but Kohl's not done yet.

298
00:17:46,680 --> 00:17:49,780
科尔的队友背叛了他  还害死了他老婆
Kohl's team betrayed him, and it got his wife killed.

299
00:17:49,790 --> 00:17:52,030
他们为求自保出卖了他
They preserved themselves over him.

300
00:17:52,160 --> 00:17:53,920
真可真不是一般的私仇
This is as personal as it gets.

301
00:17:53,920 --> 00:17:55,120
那么史戴勒在哪
So where's Steiller?

302
00:17:55,120 --> 00:17:57,190
芬奇  我在豪夫的公寓墙上
Finch, I saw the exact same pin

303
00:17:57,190 --> 00:17:59,340
看到了同样的胸针
In Hauffe's apartment.

304
00:18:02,980 --> 00:18:05,780
德裔美国人协会
The Volks American Society...

305
00:18:06,110 --> 00:18:07,770
是居住在纽约的德裔
Is an organization for New York citizens

306
00:18:07,770 --> 00:18:09,570
美国人的老乡会
Of German heritage.

307
00:18:09,570 --> 00:18:11,540
那个史塔西小组叛逃后
When the Stasi team defected,

308
00:18:11,540 --> 00:18:13,640
他们互相之间不能联系
They wouldn't have been allowed to contact each other.

309
00:18:13,640 --> 00:18:15,380
一个德国人组织能给他们三个人
A German organization would give all three

310
00:18:15,380 --> 00:18:16,940
在公开场合会面的机会
A chance to meet in public.

311
00:18:19,650 --> 00:18:22,420
那么  如果豪夫和沃尼克是会员
So, if Hauffe and Wernick were members...

312
00:18:22,420 --> 00:18:24,630
那么史戴勒肯定也是会员
Then Steiller would have been, too.

313
00:18:26,460 --> 00:18:28,120
两个犯罪现场
There are two crime scenes--

314
00:18:28,120 --> 00:18:30,160
一个在西城  一个靠近华尔街
One in the West Village, the other near Wall Street.

315
00:18:30,160 --> 00:18:32,390
同一个穿着灰西装的老年人
Now, the same senior citizen wearing a gray suit

316
00:18:32,390 --> 00:18:34,060
被人目击从两个现场离开
Was seen fleeing both locations.

317
00:18:34,060 --> 00:18:35,500
华尔街
Wall Street?

318
00:18:35,500 --> 00:18:37,910
那就是早些时候救护车被劫的地方吧
That's where the ambulance was jacked earlier, right?

319
00:18:37,910 --> 00:18:38,600
对
It sure was.

320
00:18:38,600 --> 00:18:40,240
看了那劫犯的外观描述了吗
Read the description of who jacked it?

321
00:18:40,240 --> 00:18:43,100
我追查的那人  他是怎么扯进去的
My guy? How's he involved in this?

322
00:18:43,110 --> 00:18:46,520
而这人出现在第一个案发现场还不省人事
And this guy was found unconscious at the first scene.

323
00:18:47,080 --> 00:18:48,340
伤得真漂亮
Nice bruises.

324
00:18:48,340 --> 00:18:49,780
招了没
He say anything yet,

325
00:18:49,780 --> 00:18:52,630
比如是谁把你屁股踢成了四半
Like who kicked his ass sideways?

326
00:18:52,900 --> 00:18:54,050
有倒是有  两个字
Yeah, two words--

327
00:18:54,050 --> 00:18:55,430
电话
"Phone call."

328
00:18:55,500 --> 00:18:57,260
除此之外都是德语
Everything else is in German.

329
00:19:01,520 --> 00:19:04,040
这些人里有没有你看着眼熟的
Either of these guys look familiar to you?

330
00:19:04,930 --> 00:19:06,530
好了  我们知道你是德国情报人员
Now, we know you're German intel.

331
00:19:06,530 --> 00:19:07,860
我们知道很多
We know a lot.

332
00:19:07,860 --> 00:19:09,360
如果这就是你们知道的  警察同志
If that's all you know, Polizei,

333
00:19:09,370 --> 00:19:10,210
那明显你们知道的还不够多
Then you don't know very much.

334
00:19:10,210 --> 00:19:12,870
那你为啥不跟我们说说那个老年男凶犯
Yeah, why don't you tell me about your homicidal geriatric?

335
00:19:17,040 --> 00:19:20,280
两起罪案  很危险的一个人
Two crimes, a very dangerous man at work,

336
00:19:20,280 --> 00:19:22,880
就派一个人来阻止他吗
And one agent trying to stop a killer?

337
00:19:22,880 --> 00:19:26,200
那我们这些警察同志不帮忙就太说不过去了
It'd be a shame if we polizei couldn't help.

338
00:19:27,750 --> 00:19:29,880
他叫科尔
His name is Kohl.

339
00:19:29,890 --> 00:19:31,750
他是名囚犯
He is a prisoner...

340
00:19:31,750 --> 00:19:34,490
于24年前两国政府交锋的行动中
Arrested in an operation between my government and yours

341
00:19:34,490 --> 00:19:36,150
被捕入狱
24 years ago.

342
00:19:36,860 --> 00:19:41,060
他变老了  白发苍苍  于是他们认为真老了
He had become old, feeble, they thought.

343
00:19:41,060 --> 00:19:42,900
命令下来把他转送
The order was given to transfer him

344
00:19:42,900 --> 00:19:44,800
转移到低强度监管设施
To a minimum security facility.

345
00:19:44,800 --> 00:19:46,170
那我猜是他越狱了
And I'm guessing he escaped.

346
00:19:46,170 --> 00:19:48,800
他聪明又致命
He's smart and lethal.

347
00:19:48,800 --> 00:19:50,710
他杀德国人杀了很多年
And he killed germans for years.

348
00:19:50,710 --> 00:19:52,070
没有什么比抓到他
There is nothing more important

349
00:19:52,070 --> 00:19:53,840
再把他打入天牢更重要的事情了
Than putting him back where he belongs.

350
00:19:53,840 --> 00:19:55,840
那为什么不通报美国政府
Why not involve U.S. Authorities?

351
00:19:55,840 --> 00:19:58,860
处理他并没有走司法程序
He was jailed without trial.

352
00:19:59,400 --> 00:20:01,650
他本不该存在
Kohl isn't supposed to exist.

353
00:20:01,650 --> 00:20:04,750
没人想要个国际纠纷
No one wants an international incident.

354
00:20:04,750 --> 00:20:07,320
你们本就不该在美国境内活动
You aren't supposed to be operating on U.S. Soil.

355
00:20:07,320 --> 00:20:09,260
他所到之处  必定有人要死
Where he goes, people will keep dying.

356
00:20:09,260 --> 00:20:11,030
那就帮我们  我们所求一致
Then help us. We want the same thing.

357
00:20:11,030 --> 00:20:12,130
不要在多说一个字
Don't say another word.

358
00:20:12,130 --> 00:20:13,530
喂  我们正审讯中
Hey, whoa, this is an interrogation.

359
00:20:13,530 --> 00:20:15,930
-你不能进这来  -审讯结束了
 - You can't be in here.  - This interview is over.

360
00:20:15,930 --> 00:20:18,370
我是德国使领馆的人
I am from the German Consulate,

361
00:20:18,370 --> 00:20:22,200
这是来自美国国务院的命令
And this is from the U.S. State Department--

362
00:20:22,200 --> 00:20:27,250
要求将此人立即遣返德国
Orders to extradite him back to Germany immediately.

363
00:20:29,110 --> 00:20:31,110
德裔美国人社区网站甚至连
The Volks American website wasn't even using

364
00:20:31,110 --> 00:20:33,110
像样的安全代理都不用
An open SSH secure proxy.

365
00:20:33,120 --> 00:20:34,920
几秒钟时间我就复制了他们的登录表
I cloned their log-in form in seconds.

366
00:20:34,920 --> 00:20:36,520
